The paper deals with the problem of computing join queries with functional dependencies, which is a fundamental problem in database theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses linear programming and polymatroids, which are common tools in theoretical computer science, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The paper also presents worst-case optimal algorithms, which are related to the analysis of algorithms, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses information theory to analyze the output size bound, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category.
